  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	Commands:                 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	p, pick <commit> = use commit 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	r, reword <commit> = use commit, but edit the commit message 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	e, edit <commit> = use commit, but stop for amending 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	s, squash <commit> = use commit, but meld into previous commit 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	f, fixup [-C | -c] <commit> = like "squash" but keep only the previous 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	                   commit's log message, unless -C is used, in which case 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	                   keep only this commit's message; -c is same as -C but 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	                   opens the editor 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	x, exec <command> = run command (the rest of the line) using shell 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	b, break = stop here (continue rebase later with 'git rebase --continue') 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	d, drop <commit> = remove commit 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	l, label <label> = label current HEAD with a name 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	t, reset <label> = reset HEAD to a label

  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	 - தொலைதூர பக்கத்தில் '%s' உடன் பொருந்தக்கூடிய ஒரு ref ஐத் தேடுகிறது.  
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	 - <src> தள்ளப்பட்டதா ('%s')  
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	   "refs/{தலைகள், குறிச்சொற்கள்}/" இல் ஒரு ref. அப்படியானால், அதனுடன் தொடர்புடையதாகச் சேர்க்கிறோம்  
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bfb31ba]	   refs/ {தலைகள், குறிச்சொற்கள்}/ தொலைநிலை பக்கத்தில் முன்னொட்டு.

  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	s, squash <commit> = use commit, but meld into previous commit 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	f, fixup [-C | -c] <commit> = like "squash" but keep only the previous 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	                   commit's log message, unless -C is used, in which case 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	                   keep only this commit's message; -c is same as -C but 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	                   opens the editor 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	x, exec <command> = run command (the rest of the line) using shell 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	b, break = stop here (continue rebase later with 'git rebase --continue') 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	d, drop <commit> = remove commit 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	l, label <label> = label current HEAD with a name 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	t, reset <label> = reset HEAD to a label 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	m, merge [-C <commit> | -c <commit>] <label> [# <oneline>] 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	        create a merge commit using the original merge commit's 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	        message (or the oneline, if no original merge commit was 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	        specified); use -c <commit> to reword the commit message 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	u, update-ref <ref> = track a placeholder for the <ref> to be updated 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	                      to this position in the new commits. The <ref> is 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	                      updated at the end of the rebase 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]                           
  WARNING [po/ta.po@42d0145]	These lines can be re-ordered; they are executed from top to bottom.

  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	f, fixup [-C | -c] <commit> = like "squash" but keep only the previous 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	                   commit's log message, unless -C is used, in which case 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	                   keep only this commit's message; -c is same as -C but 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	                   opens the editor 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	x, exec <command> = run command (the rest of the line) using shell 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	b, break = stop here (continue rebase later with 'git rebase --continue') 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	d, drop <commit> = remove commit 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	l, label <label> = label current HEAD with a name 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	t, reset <label> = reset HEAD to a label 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	m, merge [-C <commit> | -c <commit>] <label> [# <oneline>] 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	        create a merge commit using the original merge commit's 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	        message (or the oneline, if no original merge commit was 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	        specified); use -c <commit> to reword the commit message 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	u, update-ref <ref> = track a placeholder for the <ref> to be updated 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	                      to this position in the new commits. The <ref> is 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	                      updated at the end of the rebase 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]                           
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	These lines can be re-ordered; they are executed from top to bottom. 
  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]

  WARNING [po/ta.po@bd7dc15]	 r, மறுபரிசீலனை < உறுதி> =  உறுதிடைப் பயன்படுத்துங்கள், ஆனால்  உறுதி செய்தியைத் திருத்தவும்
